FBIS3-55798 "drsov008_o_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-008 Document Type:Daily Report 12 Jan 1994 Uzbekistan Kazakhstan President Nazarbayev Continues Visit Presidents Against Dual Citizenship LD1101161494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1202 GMT 11 Jan 94 LD1101161494 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The presidents of Kazakhstan and Uzbekistan, Nursultan Nazarbayev and Islam Karimov, have spoken out against the idea of dual citizenship, which was introduced recently by Turkmenistan, they told reporters in Tashkent Monday. Karimov, for example, has said that Russians living in Uzbekistan should believe that the republic's constitution provides them equal conditions and rights alongside the local population and other nations living in the republics. For his part, Nazarbayev said that Kazakhstan's Constitution does not offer dual citizenship and he, as the president, must obey it.
